{{See|nonplus}}
==French==

===Adverb===
'''[[non]] [[plus]]'''
# (not) [[either]]
#:''Je n'aime pas l'hiver non plus''
#::''I don't like winter [[either]]
# [[neither]]
#: ''Je n'aime pas l'hiver'' - ''Moi non plus''
#:: ''I don't like winter'' - ''Me neither''

===Usage===
''non plus'' always goes at the end of the phrase
[[Category:French language]]

==English==

The word is well adopted in the English language. 
As a verb, it means to confuse/perplex.
As a noun, it refers to a state when one can think no (non) more(plus), i.e. a state of bewilderment.